    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>Rot-Echoes are fragments of spiritual rot given semi-form by the Jarðvættr’s corruption in Phase 2. They drift toward living warmth and drain recovery with their necrotic touch. When destroyed, they leave a puddle of corrupted spiritual residue that slows movement.</p>",
      "director": "<p><strong>ABILITIES</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Rot-Touch</strong> (Main, Melee, Agility, Reach 1): T1 2 necrotic; T2 4 necrotic + target loses 1 Recovery (max 1 per hero per encounter); T3 6 necrotic + lose 1 Recovery.</li></ul><p><strong>FEATURES</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Dissolve:</strong> When destroyed, the square it occupied becomes difficult terrain.</li><li><strong>Undying Impulse:</strong> Immune to turn/fear/charm effects. Moves toward nearest living creature at start of turn if not engaged.</li></ul><p><strong>NOTES:</strong> Spawned by the Jarðvættr (Vent-Warden) in Phase 2 (Rot Corruption feature). Destroyed in a single hit (Stamina 8 = minion behavior). Beat 10 only.</p>",
